(4085, 17, 'Winter Ale', 11, 141, '6', '0', '0', 0, '', 'English Olde Ale. Traditionally malty with the warming sensation of alcohol, Olde Ales are brewed in the fall as winter warmers. Brewed in the style of an English Olde Ale, this ale balances the sweet heady aroma of spruce tips with the clean crisp finis', 0, '2010-07-22'),
