(4669, 459, 'Chateau Jiahu', 11, 126, '10', '0', '0', 0, '', '9000 year old Chateau Jiahu stands apart as the most ancient, chemically-attested alcoholic beverage in the world. Its recreation is based on painstaking excavation by Chinese archaeologists of Jiahuin the Yellow River basin, state-of-the-art microanalysi', 0, '2010-07-22'),
(4670, 1248, 'Pipe Organ Pale Ale', 3, 26, '5', '0', '0', 0, '', 'When the British introduced draught pale ale to America, the Pipe Organ Pale Ale is what they had intended. It is truly British in character. Brewed with pale ale malt and a touch of caramel malt, it has a light copper color and subtle body. The maltiness', 0, '2010-07-22'),
(4671, 1248, 'Pious Monk Dunkel', -1, -1, '5', '0', '0', 0, '', 'Gold Medal Winner of the Great American Beer Festival. Our beer is fairly dark in color, but donÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t be afraid. It is a perfect example that dark beers are not always strong beers. The body is surprisingly mellow, and the alcohol content is a bit low', 0, '2010-07-22'),
(4672, 1248, 'Millennium Trippel', 5, 61, '9', '0', '0', 0, '', 'A Belgian Trippel is a very special type of beer. A Belgian Trippel could be called the beer version of a Champagne. It is very light in color and highly carbonated giving an appearance similar to Champagne. The flavor is somewhat sweet and malty as well ', 0, '2010-07-22'),
(4673, 1248, 'Celestial Gold', 7, 77, '4', '0', '0', 0, '', 'This beer is golden in color with a light bubbly effervescence. The light body makes this lager beer appropriate for a business lunch or your evening sipping beer. The light malt flavor also accentuates the hop flavor. From the start, you will notice a fi', 0, '2010-07-22'),
(4674, 1248, 'Blast Furnace Oatmeal Stout', 1, 21, '5', '0', '0', 0, '', 'Stouts have typically been a staple beverage in the UK.  There are many variations of stouts available. You can find dry stouts, milk stouts, Imperial stouts, American stouts, and even stouts made with oats.At the Church Brew Works we have crafted delic', 0, '2010-07-22'),
(4675, 1248, 'Church Brew Oktoberfest', 7, 84, '5', '0', '0', 0, '', 'Our Oktoberfest is a light amber colored beer.  It is malty in both flavor and aroma making it a delicate beer which is very drinkable. The hop bitterness is kept low to accentuate the maltiness.  Notice the crisp clean character and enjoy.  We brewed thr', 0, '2010-07-22'),
(4676, 1248, 'Mad Brewer Maibock', 7, 91, '7', '0', '0', 0, '', 'A bock beer is required by German law to start at 17Ã‚Â°Plato.   For those who are interested, Ã‚Â°Plato is a measurement of the sugar content before fermentation.  It is a very malty lager beer with medium hop bitterness.  A maibock is a light to amber c', 0, '2010-07-22'),
(4677, 1248, 'Heavenly Hefeweizen', 4, 50, '5', '0', '0', 0, '', 'IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢m sure everyone here knows, Pittsburgh has some humid summers.  What can you do to escape the heat and enjoy yourself?  Well IÃ¢â‚¬â„¢ve got the answer.  How about a light thirst quenching Hefe Weizen (pronounced hefa Vite zen) in the cool enviro', 0, '2010-07-22'),
(4678, 1286, 'Scratch #12 2008', 3, 31, '7', '0', '0', 0, '', 'In our never-ending pursuit of answering the burning question of whatÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s new, we present Scratch #12-2008, an IPA. The IPA is a fickle beast; too much malt and you veer into a high-octane hopbomb, while too little hops can question a beerÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s', 0, '2010-07-22'),
(4679, 690, 'Jupiler', 7, 77, '5', '0', '0', 0, '', 'Jupiler is the most famous and most popular beer in Belgium. This delicious lager is brewed with the finest ingredients (malt, maize, water, hop, yeast), using undisputed craftsmanship, ensuring an outstanding beer quality. Jupiler offers refreshment on a', 0, '2010-07-22'),
(4680, 263, 'Trappist Westvleteren 12', 5, 62, '11', '0', '0', 0, '', 'This Belgian beer has an everlasting tast.  It has been choosen as the best beer in the world for several years!', 0, '2010-07-22'),
(4681, 263, 'Trappist Westvleteren Blonde', 5, 72, '6', '0', '0', 0, '', '', 0, '2010-07-22'),
(4682, 1013, 'Kate The Great Russian Imperial Stout', 3, 43, '10', '0', '0', 0, '', 'The granddaddy of stouts.  Intended for export to the Imerial Court of Russias Catherine the Great.  Jet black.  Full-bodied.  Very strong.', 0, '2010-07-22'),
(4683, 1260, 'Dark Lord Russian Imperial Stout', 3, 43, '13', '0', '0', 0, '', 'Gargantuan Russian Stout brewed with coffee, molasses, and honey.', 0, '2010-07-22'),
(4684, 1244, 'Light Weight', 3, 37, '4', '0', '0', 0, '', 'Our lightest beer, and our Bronze Medal Winner 2006 World Beer Cup German pilsner malt and American hops give this brew a light, crisp finish. Made with the light beer drinker in mind.', 0, '2010-07-22'),
(4685, 1244, 'Donovans Red', 3, 33, '5', '0', '0', 0, '', 'Named after Donovans, a 19th century Irish restaurant in downtown Waterbury. This medium-bodied, red-colored ale has a nice hop flavor and aroma.', 0, '2010-07-22'),
