(5369, 1250, 'The Livery Kilt Tilter', 1, 15, '9', '0', '0', 0, '', 'Our version of a Scotch Ale is made with a portion of peat smoked barley. Very malty, with a subtle smoky finish. Also available in a barrel aged version.', 0, '2010-07-22'),
(5370, 1250, 'Maillot Jaune', 5, 74, '6', '0', '0', 0, '', 'Maillot Jaune, or "Yellow Shirt", is named for the jersey of honor given to the leader of the Tour De France bicycle race held every July. American Lance Armstrong is the only person in history to wear the Maillot Jaune 7 times in a row! Golden in color a', 0, '2010-07-22'),
